webpackJsonp([0xdb3896773844],{571:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"Zi Huijie Blog",author:"Zi Huijie"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/home/jane/Documents/repos/web_design/zihuijie-blog/src/pages/2017-08-30-no-need-ghpages/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>I am using Gatsby to build my blog. It’s a great tool. I was trying to deploy the site through gh-pages. However, on github it only allows to use master branches to serve the site for personal pages.</p>\n<p>I did search on stackoverflow. I think I got the same answer.</p>\n<p>According to <a href="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/35978862/github-pages-why-do-i-need-a-gh-pages" target="_blank">Github pages: Why do I need a gh-pages</a>. I don’t really need to upload my blog in gh-pages. Everything should be under master.</p>\n<p>According to <a href="http://jakewiesler.com/surge-vs-github-pages-deploying-a-create-react-app-project/" target="_blank">Surge vs Github</a> I will try Surge instead.</p>\n<p>Finally, what I did with my blog is push everything under firebase, then only push the files under build folder to github pages master branch. Then I got my gh-pages.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"gh-pages need to be under master branch ?",date:"August 30, 2017"}}},pathContext:{path:"/no-need-ghpages"}}}});
//# sourceMappingURL=path---no-need-ghpages-25a57763b3106f23f6c7.js.map